comments: fell off of charging station in auton and couldn't get back up. down for the rest of the math
driver bumped into teammate a couple times, DID sometimes cycle over charge station without slowing down
They used the ground substation the most. The driver went through the charge station everytime before scoring. Good driver quick and simple.
Shuttles pieces, no intake. Tank drive so is not able to move around quickly, attempted climb early.
drops cubes if bumped, can't place them consistently at ALL, decent with cones, Driver takes too long to make decisions,

The driver's strategy was to push game pieces into their community and then pickup and place. Driver struggled in pickup/placement of cone. Randomly stopped operating in neutral zone with an entire minute remaining.
smart driver, dropped second piece to avoid penalty, cycled on the far wall, scored quickly
driver is very aware and moved out of way for teamates while still cycling. died on the field around 15 seconds before auton
Only used shelf substation. Cant pick up from the ground. Fast driver though.
Takes a long time to pickup pieces, stalled for a little bit during game, arm seems very fragile and could drop piece if hit or changes speed too quick.

intake(grabber) seems finnicky and sometimes takes a second to line up, but was consistent for the rest of the match, driver knows how to jostle the bot to get the cone in the right orientation, good bot and driver
Main strategy consisted of shoot pickups. Autom failed after successful preload. Is able to go over charge station.

Has a slow mechanic to pick up cubes from Human substation. The arm moves from the top to the bottom to pick up the cube. Also the arm if it misses a cone or the height of the arm is extended long enough it has to go down all the way down and then up. Missed two cones.
stubborn driver, wouldn't move to let teamate get to shelf before them. Went over charge station very frequently to score and very quickly. quick placement for scoring
very quick intake and scoring. good auton, likes to cycle to position 1 by the wall.
intake is good, but driver runs into teamates too much in loading zone, played nice for a double engage, can go over the charge station easily and without dropping pieces
Can move over charge station. Missed a couple cone placements. Preferred cones over cubes and had medium pace placements.

Messed 3 piece auton, didn't pick up remaining two pieces. Quick cycle time. Started on free side but starter to fill out grid on wire side, can probably do both. Goes to chute only. Picks up cubes at the end to fill out middle nodes and bottom grid.
played strong defense, had 0 penalties,
Driver had trouble lining up and grabbing cone from shelf but is very fast with scoring cones

Their robot is very clunky and unbalanced. They were bullied by more aggressive robots. Stopped operating with over a minute left. Can move over charge station. Very slow pickup and placement. But they're from Belise!!
had a very fast double engage, only goes to shelf, a little trouble going over the charge station, arm has to stay out after intaking which could cause penalties in the future
Failed 2 piece auton, started on free side but filled out grid on wire side. Went only to chute for cones, picked up cubes from ground in loading zone near end of the game.
Good driving. the arm is slow though
drove well, intake is not amazing, really likes the double substation
Pure defensive bot. Runs through the middle and tries to slow down the other team. Did not move for the first 10 seconds of teleop.
fast, stable robot. Only got cones from shute and is very good at cycling it. Slammed a teamate. Didn't score cube in auton because intake didn't outake the cube
Only places on top row with cones. Failed repeatedly to do so. Their ground pickup is slow.
Very quick robot, cube shooter, in auton shoots cubes into community. During teleop, fills out bottom grid with cubes in community and from chute. Sometimes out of control and can cause collisions.
only picks up from shelf, takes a second to intake, a bit large and slow, avoided the charge station during the match, didn't go for a stupid triple balance and instead just parked
loves double substation, very quick robot and intake
Only played defense. Attempted no pickups or placements.
got pushed so easily by 5089, only intook cubes from ground and scored in hybrid. had to get a running start onto charge station and was tippy on it
The entire robot has to rotate before actually extending the arm then it can place a cube. Fast robot but the turns make the entire robot wobble unsafely.
Only goes for cubes, usually goes for bottom grid. Usually picks from neutral zone but goes to chute near end for cubes as well.
fast and consistent across the board, schute and floor pickup, avoided the charge station during the match
very slow, intake and bot in general.
Driver is descisive and fast, failed on scoring two cones, but kept the piece in intake then scored them. Didn't drive over charge station for scoring. Works quickly with both shute and ground intake
Only went for cubes. Picked up from neutral zone and chute. Climbed with 25s left. Pretty large robot.
Predominantly places cones but can pickup cubes from the ground. Favors ground substation. Good movement throughout the field.
Really fast robot scored mostly on the bottom row but really efficient except there were quite a few traffic jams with their own teammates. started to engage with charging station early
terrible job at a triple balance, fast intake, but they place in suboptimal places
Top cube shooter bot... transfers cube from floor to top and dropped a cube when trying to score. Tipped over half way throught the match just driving by itself. Went over charge station once to scor
likes double substation, not very fast
Favors cones but failed to place repeatedly. Only used shelf substation.

Had teammates that shot cubes and cones at the team and then the robot aligned them all into the bottom row. Once the bottom row was filled it used a cube shooter to hit the top rows. Really quick cylces
balance could've been a lot faster, dropped a piece, had some trouble intaking at the start, goes over the charge station no problem
Can only collect from ground substation and can only pickup cubes. Very passive on the field.
very poor driving and defense, robot did appear to not be working correctly
Cube bot, picks up from floor and fills out hybrid first. Driver is unafraid to slam into things
really quick cycles avoided traffic with teammates by going through charge station. really smart and had to turn to place the cones and cubes in place but can rotate while moving.
Can go for cubes and cones upright on the floor. Goes to shelf for cones but struggled, dropped 2 in a row. Spent a lot of time in loading zone.
Has no fear of the charge station! But probably should have some (almost tipped over and dropped a piece), really bad balance(not entirely their fault), besides that pretty good
Main strategy was to collect cubes and ferry to community. Their Autom failed.
very quick speed and likes to intake on double substation. evades defense well.

Was being fed by pieces in neutral zone to score. Missed a couple times when trying to place cone but kept piece in intake and tried again. Was going up for charge station and tipped over when climbing
Slow elevator type mechanism to fill out the top row. Very wobbly. they picked up two pieces in auton then in teleop placed them in the bottom rows
Pancake bot with cube intake. Sort of like a cube shooter, is not very accurate. Picked up only from ground.

shelf cone cycler. had a good idea of the most advantageous places for cones to try to score links. dropped one cone in auton that was meant for high but it landed in hybrid. tried to pick up cube at shelf in the end but failed and drove to the charge station. managed to pull off a triple climb pretty well.

Never went over the charge station during cycles. Occasionally struggled to grab a piece from the double substation. When it did grab a piece, it held it high and it never unintentionally dropped a piece.

Went to pick up piece in auton but missed. Besides that they have an interesting intake that allowsd them to easily pickup from neutral zone and their elevator lets them score high consistently. Theyare good in neutral zone but can also pick up from the ground near the double station.
- very slow/inefficient driving at start, sped up as teleop progressed, still mediocre though- good intake speed- was blocked from engaging by charge station side at auton
just stopped mid way in their match
Took a big hit and was defended. No penalties. decided to go score in their lane rather than immediately completing a link.

Drew a penalty for having their arm out and hitting a bot. Really focused on getting peieces from chute and got in alliance members' way to get there. Could score high fairly well but when they tried to score mid, they just dropped it and then pushed it in
Had an elevator system that made it top heavy/tipsy when the elevator was up. Didn't travel over the charge station.

- tipped on side of charge station in auton, saved during teleop (took some time though)- after that incident, very fast intake/driving/placing- seemed like"supercharge" was intentional (cone stacking, aimed), but was on high, 80 seconds left, not close grid, so i have no idea why they would do that

very fast robot. has a very unique swivel arm that they use to the upmost potential. tried to pull off a 3 piece auton but dropped the last game piece. did a very good job climbing as well. picked up mainly from the shelf.
helped 910 successfully get off charge station at start because they were stuck, good teamwork, a bit slow in general though, not bad. dropped a cone
not defended much, had a piece snatched from them despite the forks. focused on their "lane".
no show
efficient scoring, evaded defense quite well
tried to play some defense but racked up some fouls. did not play very good defense. made no effort whatsoever at offense though it has the facilities to do so.

Really quick to move back and forth from chute and scoring position but was a bit antsy when they were intaking. Trying to leave before fully taking in pieces. Scored by going around charge station and auton missed pieces with pauses in the middle
- consistent/fast driving/intake, good and organized placing (made 2 links independently)
got defended heavily against.
did good manuevering, double intake,
- double engage- good speed, but did miss some pieces and flung one in the air

Didn't use any machinery. Pushed cubes (but not cones) around the whole time. Did travel over the charge station once. Later in the match, it just stayed in the community and didn't do much. (last 40ish seconds)

scored pretty consistently. a cube got in the way at the chute and they spent quite a few seconds getting it out of the way. seemed to be a bit aggressive against own team mates in loading zone in one instance. tried desperately to do a last second climb but failed.
decent mobility, but kind of tippy. not really defended against. were flexible and did not stay in their lane.

Struggled intaking cubes and needed a teammate to push them in for them if they could not get it from slamming into the wall, Pretty slow and only scored low. Intake is too deep into robot's frame for it to be consistent w/ the cubes and they only tried cones in preload
human player is SLOW, added atleast 5 sec to each cycle because of it, cycled over charge station

At the start of teleop, its outake stopped working which really messed up the driver. It tried to play defense to little avail. It pushed a blue bot into its own zone which i believe gave itself a foul. (I may be wrong)
ground intake is a bit slow. did nothing in auton. has good speed while moving, though.
- double engage, but shaky and almost failed a few times- ok speed, good placing, but intake is very slow- dropped several pieces

Intake pieces after human player drops them from shelf (emphasis on drops from shelf) where it land in the intake. They then score by having their arm go up and over the robot where it seems like the cone is always just going to fall out Had problems keeping cones in intake and missing the mid node since they had to take the arm going over bot into consideration. They do prefer to cylce over the charge station though
They're like us, but not as good. They will score in all "lanes". Their piece security is not the best and they got defended a bit
fast robot, small, only cubes. dropped cubes a few times but picked back up
Kind of slow to grab and score pieces. Seemed lost at times. Never cycled over the charge station.
#NAME?
did some soccerballing in the neutral zone at the beginning of the game for the hybrid nodes. did some shelf cone cycling. seemed to have some trouble climbing but managed to do so anyway.

Tippy and not very fast. Even though it was not defended, the driver did not seem to know what they were doing, slammed into the substations multiple times, and scored high instead of actually making a link. There was some contact in frame perimeter, but unclear if penalty was called. the arm is a liability.

Super fast cycle times but they grab most of their pieces from the chute. Showed ability to pick up from ground but avoided getting near the charge station until endgame. Much more comfortable scoting mid and driver made informed decisions once he saw that his alliance mates were getting the high nodes letting them leave the high scores and letting them go mid. Auton is a bit shakymissing pieces though
The bot seemed very rickety. Never cycled over the charge station. Struggled to score at some points
robot is so clunky and tippy, too big,
it is difficult for them to line up and recieve the cubes. they are also very jerky and inconsistent when they move. They were not defended. their piece security is subpar. they shoot cubes.
uses cube shooter pretty well. missed a cargo in auton. there were the slightest instances of driver indecision but the driver generally handled it pretty well.

- auton very slow place, no mobility, although much time left- very inconsistent speed, generally slow- probably broke, as it stopped in place for much of mid to late teleop (was able to get park, then froze again)- wobbly

intereeting scoring mechanism, but never accurate on first try. auton neutral zone pickup failed

Drew fouls with arm. Intake stopped working and dragging across field so they played lackluster defense causing some penalties. Eventually stowed arm inside perimeter but did not do well on defense. Didnt communicate well w/ alliance member causing a failed engagement
Able to avoid defense decently.
Seemed lost for most of the match. A bit top heavy. Never cycled over the charge station. Struggled to actually go and grab pieces on top of struggling to score them
had a bit of trouble picking up cones on the ground but that was rare. tried very hard to get on the charge station but time was too much of a constraint.
- double engage- dropped cube just before trying to place (wheels turned too early?)- good speed, but finds it hard to dodge other robots- organized placer

- good triple engage- fast, but not very elegant driving -- crashes into stuff a lot- placing speed high, accuracy ok
got defended but avoided it sometimes.
dysfunctional intake, so no scoring. yet, no effort to defend, just jittered around in middle of field. extremely difficult engage but made it work after 15s.yikes
Failed at charge station getting park points. Kind of slow. Picked up pieces from shelf but were slow to intake them. Need to cldan up accuracy for both intake and scoring.
pretty quick robot. though it is tank, the driver is pretty good. focused a bit on hybrid nodes at one point. missed the mid node that would have won them the match if 135 climbed as well.

Tipped slightly off of the charge station inorder to allow for a triple climb. Hanged out in the community a bit to clean up some left over pieces.  Held the pieces very securely. Did not cycle over the charge station.

- last second triple engage- good, fast, consistent low scorer of cubes (no cones?)- has a bit of trouble dodging robots- engage/mobility prevented in auton because charge station blocked them- cycles over charge station!

Good at intaking quickly but had top node accuracy issue. Came back to score from around charge station. Pretty fast but i would like to see them pick up more from neutral zone. ANd pick a preference it seems like its high but they missed a bit
great auton, consistent cone scoring from chute (like us!). generally avoided going over charge station. cool display on side of bot.
tank, rough driving, one foul, only scored on the bottom row. clanky and wobbly

attemped a strong auton but missed slightly due to both coding and alliance partners knocking pieces. medium speed but but a good driver. favors cyling to shelf and scoring high.

dropped a piece, played nice to teamates in loading zone, auton didn't work/they couldm't climb up the charge station
Very good at dodging traffic in the middle and keeping a fast cycle time. Attempted to go over charge station to score but descided against it.

Got pushed into a corner by a red and couldnt escape and thus resulted in a foul by 316. Really fast cycles and went through the charge station to avoid traffic except it was slow when going through it.
Collects cubes from ground substation and scores in hybrid nodes. They can score in mid nodes. Semi-aggressive.
penalty for hitting bot in loading zone, can pickup cones and cubes from ground, works on their own area before others.

intake is pretty fast!, bot just runs into shelf and it works out, auton looks good, goes over the charge station frequently and easily, played nice for a triple balance

clanky robot. missed cones frequently. super slow when transporting cones
Collects cubes from ground and cones from ground substation. Not afraid to get physical.
quick cycle time, works on their area, goes for links, cones and then fills cube, goes to chute for cones and picks up cubes from ground.
seems to prefer cubes to cones, maybe because they score them faster. went over charge station a few times but not fast. driver kind of wandered off cycle path sometimes for no discernable reason.
they had some trouble with one cone that they dropped twice, they accidentally knocked a cone over into the double substation temporarily jamming it, missed a cone, not a great bot
Very slow over all, VERY tippy and almost got tipped over by opponent, cant handle defence and got pushed around.
great auton. gathered all pieces, mostly cones, from chute. driver is direct but bot isnt super fast.
Great at maneuvering around the field. Collects cubes and cones at shelf substation and is great at placing. Autom is simple.

did not do much. scored very slowly.
Good at pickup from shelf and unafraid to go over charge station for scoring. Unsure about some cube placements for scoring

driver sometimes forgets what he's doing, intake can be slow,they didn't score during auton for some reason

while they are very fast and score quickly, they ran into their own teammates a couple of times

really efficient driver. smart choices to avoid the other team's defense. can fill all rows with the arm

So fast with intaking pieces off the ground from shute and cycling to score instantly. Went over charge station to score once
Cones directly from ground substation and cubes from the ground. Hybrid nodes for cubes. High/mid for cones.

cube shooter, missed almost every shot but worked effectively as a ferry
missed their auton. the driver had poor communication with team resulting in multiple crashes with teammates

driver is really good(always looking for opertunities to promote pieces driving around traffic etc.), got a 2 second double balance singlehandedly
cycled over charge station, missed a couple of shots. pretty quick scorer
quick manuvering. can only pick up cones from the shelf substation. two fouls

cube shooter, but not a great one, struggled to score mid point-blank, had trouble getting directly from schute, generally not great driving

defensive bot. it is a kitbot with what appears to be an intake but is unused. not a very good defensive bot because it is easily pushed around. did climb pretty well, though.
fast enough to get from charge station to community without much chance for defense. are able to go through any lane. balances very quickly
maneuverable

dropped a cone once, couldnt cycle over charge station
everybot, so pretty tippy. the driver is decent, but he does not really handle well the turning around transition between the loading station and the community. he turns around when he gets ther

It only grabs cubes. The cubes are secure and can't be knocked out. Decently fast cycle times. Does not cycle over the charge station.
cube shooter allows them to ferry cubes. They take a while at the single substation. They aren't that fast so they can be defended against and their driving is a little jerky at times.

nothing remarkable, decent intake
- triple engage- good speed/ general efficiency
they took a rest for about minute, came back to life. Driving quality is not great as they are slow. It is difficult to intake.
pretty fast bot and fast shelf cycler and scorer. it can intake cubes from the shelf. has a pretty sweet auton as well.
Helped to pick up ground cargo. Almost tipped ccoming right out of auton. Did not cycle over the charge station. It received cones the way Tars does. This might (?) be useful

Fast chute and score bot. They engage w/ the charge station by flipping onto it from the side. They go over the charge station a lot during cycles and they are still insanely fast and also spent some time scoring by pushing in slightly out of place pieces. Can pick up from ground as well
Cone balanced on top in auton then falls when they drive cable side and they push it in. just played lackluster defense the whole time and w/ around 45 seconds left they stopped moving

fast for the size, props to driver, still very shaky, cyclying over charge

goat

efficient scorer, traffic jammed

fine until it stalled out midgame on the charge station

they move decently. They got defended heavily multiple times.

clunky and gigantic

only scored low, but did it rather effectively. one cube slipped out of the intake at one instance. the auton missed its last cube.

ferried a lot of cubes. They move well, but they are not defended. Alliance did not capitalize off of their efforts
moved efficiently but wasnt defended against
Very quick engagement. Didn't cycle over the charge station. Like to grab from the ground or from the double substation.

Bumpy drivetrain and a shooter that shoots completely vertically. They back up and then push it in low they also found a strategy to push their piece that they want against the wall to get it deep enough so that they can grab the piece, still dont like it

cannot intake from the ground, only the shelf. this does not pair well with the fact that the intake dropped cargo twice that could have been the difference between winning and losing. otherwise, it is a pretty quick bot with a very good driver.

just stood in the center for almost a minute, drive rrain failure possibly

efficient driver. auton was rough. cycles were really fast

goes for only cones in teleop, really big robot, fills out whatever is available.
